summary: I had the random idea that Arya, while in the HoBaW, would invent a brand new poison for giving the gift of mercy. It would not...
body:
I had the random idea that Arya, while in the HoBaW, would invent a brand new poison for giving the gift of mercy. It would not only provide a quick, painless death to whoever drank it, but would warm and tighten the body so that it feels in their last seconds like they’re getting a hug.

And it would be called Mother’s Embrace, because it would be as comforting and peaceful a way to die as being rocked to sleep in your mother’s arms. And also because it gives you the Mother’s mercy and sends you into death’s embrace.

But then the whole thing would get an ironic twist when she feeds it to Lady Stoneheart, and thus her own mother would die in her embrace rather than vice versa.

And now I’m in pain, so.

summary: Sometimes I think about things in ASOIAF and how GOT probably won’t address them.   Like...if Arya and Varys cross paths and...
body:
Sometimes I think about things in ASOIAF and how GOT probably won’t address them.  

Like…if Arya and Varys cross paths and Varys is all, “I searched and searched for you, where the fuck did you go?”  Because she was a tiny child who managed to hide from his spies so well Littlefinger had to recruit somebody to pretend to be her.  And then nobody fucking heard from her, like ever again.

And Arya’s just like, “The House of Black and White, valar morghulis, motherfucker.”

And sirens just start blaring in Varys’ head.  Because he knows goddamn well what they do there and how she could’ve hidden there for so long.  The House of the Black and White isn’t a damn orphanage, it’s a fucking assassin training house.  Just imagine how that fucks up his schemes, like a wrench a mile wide just tossed in there.
